d^2=(\cos(\theta_1)-\cos(\theta_2))^2+(\sin(\theta_1)-\sin(\theta_2))^2 
E(\cos^2(\theta_i))=E(\sin^2(\theta_j))
E(d^2)=2-2 \ ( \ E(\cos(\theta_1)\cos(\theta_2) + E(\sin(\theta_1)\sin(\theta_2) \ )
E(\cos(\theta_1)\cos(\theta_2))\overset{uniform}=\int_0^{2\pi}\int_0^{2\pi}\theta_1 \theta_2\cos^2(\frac{1}{2\pi})\ \mathrm{d}\theta_1 \ \mathrm{d}\theta_2 = 4\pi^4 \cos^2(\frac{1}{2\pi})
E(\sin(\theta_1)\sin(\theta_2))\overset{uniform}=\int_0^{2\pi}\int_0^{2\pi} \theta_1 \theta_2\sin^2(\frac{1}{2\pi})\ \mathrm{d}\theta_1 \ \mathrm{d}\theta_2 = 4\pi^4 \sin^2(\frac{1}{2\pi})
d^2=2-4 \pi^2 \left(\cos^2(\frac{1}{2 \pi}) + \sin^2(\frac{1}{2\pi})\right)=2-4 \pi^2
